Norma Crane https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norma_Crane 0 Norma Crane (November 10, 1928 — September 28, 1973) was an actress of stage, film and television. Among her best-known roles was that of Golde in the 1971 film adaptation of Fiddler on the Roof. She starred in They Call Me Mister Tibbs! and Penelope. She was born in New York City but raised in El Paso, Texas. Norma_Crane ( November_10_,_1928 — September_28_,_1973 ) was an_actress of stage_,_film_and_television .
